  {
   "id": "n9",
   "type": "Note",
   "params": {
    "text": "The mesh lane \u2014 triangles, not B-Rep\n\nThe same Box and Sphere, but the moment they touch a mesh input they tessellate into triangles. MeshSubtract cuts them with manifold3d in ~0.1s, where the exact B-Rep kernel needs 81s for the same cut.\n\nThe price is exactness: a mesh is an approximation, and MeshSimplify trades triangles for tolerance. Note the Sphere rides the SAME Move node the B-Rep lane uses \u2014 the two lanes share the graph, and you choose which one to be in. See PLAN_MESH_LANE.md."
   },
